<div id="review_3457902310" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3457902310" />
    <a title="Loretta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18967405-loretta"><img alt="Loretta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1622498132p2/18967405.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3457902310?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Loretta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Loretta" href="/user/show/18967405-loretta">Loretta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781788282574" href="/book/show/39102308-the-railway-children">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18967405-loretta?shelf=children">children</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18967405-loretta?shelf=classic">classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18967405-loretta?shelf=my-2020-reading-challenge">my-2020-reading-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18967405-loretta?shelf=august-2020">august-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3457902310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer782107203863314091">I feel that there are many children’s classics that should have been read when one was young. For me, this was one of those classics. It was a nice enough story with each chapter filled with a good, solid, moral message for children, but again, as the story evolved, the ending was “tied up in a bow” and the characters world was set right again. Three stars for the writing.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

