        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3371967586" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11968764816695173005">Having watched and enjoyed both film versions when I was younger, I was generally surprised to discover that I had never read the original classic until now. Set in London and a small rural village in the heart of the English countryside, three children (Bobby, Peter and Phyllis) are stunned when they have to leave the city lights and into a cottage in the middle of nowhere. Their father has been taken away from them and their mother won&apos;t reveal the main reason why. Meanwhile, the three childre</span>
  <span id="freeText11968764816695173005" style="display:none">Having watched and enjoyed both film versions when I was younger, I was generally surprised to discover that I had never read the original classic until now. Set in London and a small rural village in the heart of the English countryside, three children (Bobby, Peter and Phyllis) are stunned when they have to leave the city lights and into a cottage in the middle of nowhere. Their father has been taken away from them and their mother won't reveal the main reason why. Meanwhile, the three children (siblings) explore the area and end up frequent visitors to the railway station. There's a ton of adventures both pleasant and scary. It brought me lots of nostalgic memories for me from childhood. Enjoyed! </span>
  <a data-text-id="11968764816695173005" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
