<div id="review_3448048692" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3448048692" />
    <a title="Ruth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11771264-ruth"><img alt="Ruth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623698411p2/11771264.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3448048692?book_show_action=true">Jul 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ruth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ruth" href="/user/show/11771264-ruth">Ruth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11771264-ruth?shelf=classics-childrens">classics-childrens</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11771264-ruth?shelf=challenge-12-l-l-to-tea-2020">challenge-12-l-l-to-tea-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3448048692" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7804772846534958929">The Railway Children was a such a beautiful story. <br/>In this sweet enduring classic, <br/>set in the Edwardian era, is a tale <br/>and adventures of three siblings: <br/>Roberta &quot;Bobbie, the oldest at <br/>twelve years old who is a wise <br/>and determine young girl, Peter, <br/>the man of the house, a brave and <br/>clever boy sees himself as a leader; <br/>Phyllis, &quot;Phil&quot; the adorable and <br/>bubbly youngest sister with a <br/>very forgiving nature.<br/><br/>When their father is mysteriously <br/>taken away by two men, their <br/>mother moves them to the country </span>
  <span id="freeText7804772846534958929" style="display:none">The Railway Children was a such a beautiful story. <br />In this sweet enduring classic, <br />set in the Edwardian era, is a tale <br />and adventures of three siblings: <br />Roberta "Bobbie, the oldest at <br />twelve years old who is a wise <br />and determine young girl, Peter, <br />the man of the house, a brave and <br />clever boy sees himself as a leader; <br />Phyllis, "Phil" the adorable and <br />bubbly youngest sister with a <br />very forgiving nature.<br /><br />When their father is mysteriously <br />taken away by two men, their <br />mother moves them to the country <br />where they settle in a white house <br />with three chimneys. <br />As she sets to work to sell her <br />stories as a means to support her <br />family; to lighten her burden,<br />the children take it upon themselves <br />to help her with tasks and chores<br />around the house. <br /><br />Drawn to the railway line:<br />"They make sure that they are <br />close by when, Green Dragon, the <br />9:15 am train is passing by, and <br />they wave to the passengers, and <br />out of first class, the hand of an <br />older man waves back. <br />This becomes a routine for the children."<br />"Take our love to Father" the children cried.<br /><br />Exploring their surroundings, <br />they come to know the locals offering<br />friendship, help, acts of kindness and <br />bravery in dangerous situations.<br /><br />The authoress delivery of this heart <br />warming story in simple prose <br />highlights the values exhibited<br />by the characters, making this an <br />ideal choice for parents and children <br />to read and discuss together.<br />It was delightful to read about <br />youngsters that loved and honored <br />their parents, respected and cared <br />about people, knowing the importance <br />in doing the right thing. I missed out <br />in reading this book in my my childhood,<br />but if I had, I would have loved it every<br />bit as much as I do today.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7804772846534958929" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


